Typing

Rules for creating an identifier
1.  Can’t use a reserved word mainly because it will make confusion
    for the compiler as well as it will give an error.
    >>> break = 1
    SyntaxError: invalid syntax
2.  Can’t start an identifier with a digit (0-9)
    >>> 123varname = 1
    SyntaxError: invalid syntax
3.  Should not contain any special character other than A-Z, a-z, _e
    >>> var$name=1
    File "<stdin>", line 1
        var$name=1
           ^
        SyntaxError: invalid syntax
4.  Don't use double underscores (_) in the beginning and at the end of the variable name
    ie: __private__, __len__
    because python use these to create special variables or functions in framework classes.